OH THIS IS MAGNIFICENT. Okay, here's how to split this chaos three ways:
##Person 1: The Database Ringmaster ðŸ¦†
Files: app/db/, app/models/, app/utils/sql_safety.py
Your mission:

Set up DuckDB with hilariously random data (tables like unicorn_sightings, pizza_toppings_by_mood, failed_startups)
Build the SQL safety validator (block DROP/DELETE, add timeouts)
Create the data models for fight logs
Vibe: You're building the arena. Make the data absurd enough that agents have fun stuff to query

Key deliverables:

duckdb_init.py - creates connection, seeds tables
sql_safety.py - validates queries are SELECT-only
fight_log.py - Pydantic models for rounds/results


##Person 2: The AI Whisperer ðŸ§ 
Files: app/agents/, app/core/scoring.py
Your mission:

Build the agent system that generates SQL queries via LLM
Write prompts that make agents increasingly unhinged ("Your opponent just used 3 CTEs. Embarrass them.")
Create the complexity/fun scoring system (points for window functions, recursive CTEs, chaos)
Vibe: You're the agent's voice. Make them trash-talk in SQL comments

Key deliverables:

base_agent.py - SQLAgent interface
openai_agent.py - LLM integration (Claude API works too if you want!)
scoring.py - calculates how absurd each query is


##Person 3: The Showrunner ðŸŽ­
Files: app/core/fight_manager.py, app/ui/streamlit_app.py, app/config.py
Your mission:

Build the fight orchestrator (manages rounds, executes queries, handles errors)
Create the Streamlit UI with live updates
Add dramatic flair (animated emojis when queries fail, victory screens)
Vibe: WWE announcer energy. This UI should make people lose their minds

Key deliverables:

fight_manager.py - runs the fight loop, coordinates agents & DB
streamlit_app.py - the visual spectacle
config.py - settings like rounds, timeouts, API keys


